==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reconstruction
<hw>Re`con*struc"tion</hw> <pr>(-str?k"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of constructing again; the state of being
reconstructed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(U.S. Politics)</fld> <def>The act or process of
reorganizing the governments of the States which had passed ordinances
of secession, and of reestablishing their constitutional relations to
the national government, after the close of the Civil War.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reconstructive</ent>⟦br⟧
